1
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:22,867
Mikoy can't come and he sent me
as a replacement.

2
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:25,133
Good morning.

3
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,433
My name is Evangeline Macapugay.

4
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:32,500
I'm your temporary probationary
officer, Celeste.

5
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,700
It's Celeste, silent E.

6
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:37,700
How are you?

7
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:39,867
Oh my God, my life
is super surreal.

8
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:44,733
Imagine, the city hall replaced
the officer assigned to me.

9
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:46,167
They gave me a dictator.

10
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:48,400
And not just that,
not just that.

11
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:50,133
She asked me to remove
my accessories.

12
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,833
I feel so naked.

13
00:00:52,900 --> 00:00:53,967
Don't worry.

14
00:00:54,033 --> 00:00:56,100
You're still beautiful
whatever you do.

15
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:58,600
- Water break...
- Didn't I tell you,

16
00:00:58,667 --> 00:01:01,100
you're not allowed to accept
calls while on duty?

17
00:01:01,167 --> 00:01:03,967
What do you not understand?

18
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:05,400
I'll call you back.

19
00:01:05,467 --> 00:01:08,400
I'll add one hundred hours
to your community service.

20
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:10,233
You know what?

21
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:11,733
You...

22
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:13,867
you're right.

23
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:15,967
Manila became bad for her.

24
00:01:16,033 --> 00:01:18,533
But she acts now as if she's
a legitimate native of Manila.

25
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:20,733
She seemed ashamed of where
she came from.

26
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:23,100
Maybe if I didn't leave her
in Manila,

27
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:24,867
I could've guided her properly.

28
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:26,633
You're too hard on yourself.

29
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,000
You're too much.

30
00:01:28,067 --> 00:01:29,500
I'm serious.

31
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:31,333
But I won't give up on her.

32
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:34,033
I will introduce her
to the old Celeste.

33
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,300
I'm upset.

34
00:01:35,367 --> 00:01:36,333
Don't come near me.

35
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,333
Don't ever come near me.

36
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,833
Sebastian, what are you
doing here?

37
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:42,333
Father asked me to bring that
to you.

38
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:43,500
You forgot it.

39
00:01:43,567 --> 00:01:44,700
That's your food.

40
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:48,200
Can you please remind them
that I don't eat this?

41
00:01:48,267 --> 00:01:50,067
And besides, I'm not a child.

42
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:52,133
I don't need him to do this
for me.

43
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:54,600
Okay, so I'll just take it home.

44
00:01:54,667 --> 00:01:56,267
That's fine.

45
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:57,333
Just leave it there.

46
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:59,167
How can you handle Celeste?

47
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:00,833
Why? What happened?

48
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:03,100
She doesn't know how
to follow the rules.

49
00:02:03,167 --> 00:02:04,867
Take it easy with Celeste.

50
00:02:04,933 --> 00:02:07,500
I'm planning to make a
recommendation to Mayor.

51
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:09,933
That is to push through
with the case against her.

52
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,067
No, don't.

53
00:02:11,133 --> 00:02:13,300
Celeste is still an Uragon.

54
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:15,300
She is a little troublemaker.

55
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:17,233
Be patient with her, please.

56
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:20,233
I hope this is the last time
that I will confiscate that.

57
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:21,367
And my punishment?

58
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:22,467
It will still push through.

59
00:02:22,533 --> 00:02:25,433
You're such an angel.

60
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:27,167
We're done for the day.

61
00:02:27,233 --> 00:02:29,133
Don't be late tomorrow.

62
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:32,067
Do we understand each other?

63
00:02:32,133 --> 00:02:33,533
Is Mikoy still on leave?

64
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:36,000
Unfortunately, yes.

65
00:02:36,067 --> 00:02:37,700
I'm still your guardian.

66
00:02:37,767 --> 00:02:39,100
Such a delight.

67
00:02:39,167 --> 00:02:40,433
See you tomorrow.

68
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,567
See you.

69
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,167
Good day.

70
00:03:03,367 --> 00:03:05,233
Are you okay there?

71
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:08,967
Mother, Father?

72
00:03:09,033 --> 00:03:10,767
Did you already give Celeste
her food?

73
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:15,667
- What's the update?
- Yes, but she won't eat it.

74
00:03:15,733 --> 00:03:17,867
You're just wasting
your efforts, Father.

75
00:03:17,933 --> 00:03:20,533
What's important is
she accepted it.

76
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:26,100
I'm glad you're not discouraged
to get close to your daughter.

77
00:03:27,933 --> 00:03:31,700
I just hope that she will soften
little by little.

78
00:03:31,767 --> 00:03:35,300
Your relationship will go back
to what it was before.

79
00:03:35,367 --> 00:03:38,033
You look so much alike.

80
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:41,467
I'm sure you are always
in her heart and mind.

81
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:47,600
Father, you and Celeste
are like this,

82
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:49,267
a fruit split into two.

83
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:52,567
Hey, you're wrong.

84
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:55,967
Celeste will get mad.

85
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:57,900
For her, the only person
she looks like

86
00:03:57,967 --> 00:04:00,033
is her mother, Lucinda.

87
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,433
She doesn't even use
my last name.

88
00:04:04,567 --> 00:04:07,500
You know, Celeste is just like
a Pili nut.

89
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:10,433
You have to work hard on her.

90
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:14,833
You will wait for the right time
before you can harvest it.

91
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:16,633
Once you harvest it,

92
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:18,533
you should have the patience
to crack it open.

93
00:04:19,533 --> 00:04:23,500
At first, it's hard but
when you get used to it,

94
00:04:23,567 --> 00:04:26,867
you won't notice that
you're making a lot.

95
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:30,433
Celeste is just tough now.

96
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:33,433
But eventually,
you can soften her heart.

97
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:36,067
There's nothing love can't do.

98
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:38,367
Just have patience.

99
00:04:38,433 --> 00:04:40,367
I'll help you, okay?

100
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:49,800
Okay, let's go back to work.

101
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,733
You too.

102
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,600
You don't want to help?

103
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:01,567
I'll just eat here,
Father, Mother.

104
00:05:01,667 --> 00:05:03,367
You will just eat.

105
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,300
Hi, Tonito.

106
00:05:40,367 --> 00:05:42,633
We weren't able to talk earlier
in the office.

107
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:44,133
I was there.

108
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:47,033
I guess you are in hurry
to go there to Palawan.

109
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:53,167
I presumed Vivian already
told you what happened earlier.

110
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:54,167
Yes.

111
00:05:54,233 --> 00:05:57,300
She told me that you argued.

112
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,567
Is she still mad?

113
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:01,433
Let her be.

114
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,933
You should get used to it.

115
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,200
She must be so stressed.

116
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:06,933
Just understand her.

117
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,800
That's what I always do.

118
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:10,767
If only I don't have
almond-shaped eyes,

119
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:15,167
I will think that I'm adopted
because she's so grouchy at me.

120
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:18,467
You never fail to make me laugh.

121
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:20,033
Why did you call?

122
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:25,767
Oh yeah, I was wondering,
did you talk to Tiff today?

123
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:27,933
I can't contact her.

124
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:32,567
I'm not used to waking up
without a text or call from her.

125
00:06:32,633 --> 00:06:35,033
Don't worry.
She's doing fine in Sorsogon.

126
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:38,233
That's good to know.

127
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:41,100
I've been restless.

128
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,267
Oh, Tonito?

129
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:46,100
- Why?
- Are you free for dinner later?

130
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:48,567
Can you come to my place
after work?

131
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:51,167
I'll cook your favorite
 bakalaw dish.

132
00:06:51,233 --> 00:06:53,133
What's the occasion?

133
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,267
I just want to celebrate
my small victory.

134
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,033
I'll tell you about it later.

135
00:06:58,033 --> 00:07:00,333
I'm really happy for you
whatever it is

136
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:03,033
but I'm sorry,
I can't make it tonight.

137
00:07:03,100 --> 00:07:05,567
I have an appointment
with our wedding planner.

138
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,867
Can't you move that?

139
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:10,667
I seldom invite you for dinner.

140
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:13,033
Celeste begged me about that.

141
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,567
I'm sorry, I can't.

142
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:18,633
No need to apologize.

143
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,333
Of course, I understand.

144
00:07:21,467 --> 00:07:23,333
Maybe next time?

145
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,433
Sure, no problem.

146
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,733
Father, there's still dirt
on the plate.

147
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,000
- Huh?
- Look.

148
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:46,133
I didn't see that.

149
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,600
You are getting old.

150
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,500
What do you mean old?
Who is old?

151
00:07:49,567 --> 00:07:51,600
It's Sebastian.

152
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:53,433
He is.

153
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:55,733
Ouch!

154
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:58,300
Love, what happened?

155
00:07:58,367 --> 00:07:59,867
Love, look.

156
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:00,933
You are wounded.

157
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:03,233
Celeste? Celeste...

158
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,600
get alcohol and cotton.

159
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:06,767
Blow it.

160
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:11,767
Love, you're working too hard.

161
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:13,333
You should rest.

162
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,767
I slept late last night.

163
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:17,233
I didn't notice that
I fell asleep.

164
00:08:18,367 --> 00:08:20,233
You're working too hard.

165
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,867
Here it is, Father.

166
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:24,033
Here it is, wait.

167
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:25,567
It looks like that will hurt.

168
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:29,833
It's just like an ant bite.

169
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:32,300
Ah! That hurts.

170
00:08:32,367 --> 00:08:34,267
We have to clean that.

171
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:35,900
You might get tetanus.

172
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:38,433
Kiss it, kiss it.

173
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:40,667
That's okay.
I already cleaned it.

174
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:42,367
Here, here.

175
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:44,467
- There's pain here also.
- Does it also hurt?

176
00:08:44,533 --> 00:08:46,300
Really, okay.

177
00:08:46,367 --> 00:08:47,667
And here as well.

178
00:08:47,733 --> 00:08:50,800
Oh, Mother is acting silly.

179
00:08:50,867 --> 00:08:52,367
Here, here.

180
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,767
Come, Celeste.

181
00:08:55,867 --> 00:09:00,733
Let me kiss my very kind
daughter.

182
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:05,667
Mother is like a child.

183
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:06,900
She's jealous.

184
00:09:06,967 --> 00:09:10,200
She intentionally hurt herself
so I can kiss her.

185
00:09:10,267 --> 00:09:11,667
She wants to be treated sweetly.

186
00:09:13,033 --> 00:09:16,533
Of course not.

187
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,733
But what I said is true.

188
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:18,933
You should rest.

189
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,700
- You're working too hard.
- I'm almost done.

190
00:09:20,767 --> 00:09:23,300
It's almost finished.

191
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:24,467
You should rest.

192
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:26,067
Yes, it's almost finished.

193
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:31,533
It's her.

194
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,200
Oh my!

195
00:09:33,267 --> 00:09:35,933
You're already old and
you're acting like a child.

196
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:40,333
You're already old and
you're acting like a child.

197
00:09:46,567 --> 00:09:48,900
Celeste, you're here.

198
00:09:48,967 --> 00:09:50,433
Celeste, how was your food?

199
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:51,967
Is it delicious?

200
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,833
I gave it to the dogs.

201
00:09:57,733 --> 00:09:59,600
Celeste is terrible.

202
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:04,000
She said earlier that she will
give her food to her co-workers.

203
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,767
But she gave it to the dogs.

204
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:11,633
Those are organic fruits
and vegetables.

205
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:15,667
Believe me, she ate them.

206
00:10:17,067 --> 00:10:18,733
How can you say that?

207
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:21,833
She said she gave it
to the dogs.

208
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:25,833
There's no fruitarian
and vegetarian dog.

209
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:27,333
She ate them.

210
00:10:40,667 --> 00:10:44,300
I thought that after
a long time,

211
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:47,167
my longing for you will subside,
Mother.

212
00:10:48,367 --> 00:10:50,933
This place is so different
without you.

213
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:57,733
I can never call this
home again.

214
00:11:33,933 --> 00:11:35,300
Vivian, wait.

215
00:11:40,067 --> 00:11:43,000
Did you ask the finance
to hold my salary?

216
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,233
Yes, I did.

217
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,967
Why?

218
00:11:47,033 --> 00:11:48,300
Why not?

219
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:52,067
Because I work here,
I work for you.

220
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:56,867
Do you expect me to reward
your bad performance?

221
00:11:58,267 --> 00:11:59,933
I just graduated.

222
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:06,933
I did not use that excuse
when I was in your shoes.

223
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:09,933
Here...

224
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:14,467
hold onto that because it could
be your last.

225
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:18,233
Because as long as you
haven't proved something,

226
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:21,633
you will not receive
anything from me.

227
00:12:53,933 --> 00:12:55,333
Is there something wrong?

228
00:12:57,433 --> 00:13:00,900
Haven't I proved anything,
Winston?

229
00:13:00,967 --> 00:13:02,233
What do you mean?

230
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:04,467
Am I still that worthless
fresh graduate

231
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:07,400
that Vivian said back then?

232
00:13:07,467 --> 00:13:08,933
Don't tell me,

233
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:12,533
for the longest time that you've
been running this business,

234
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:15,333
you still feel insecure.

235
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:22,600
Vivian gave this to me
years ago when I was new here.

236
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:26,067
I haven't proven anything.

237
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:31,333
And until now she still
sees me this way.

238
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:34,100
I'm still a loose change,
worthless.

239
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:37,733
Do you expect that Vivian
will praise you?

240
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:41,800
You know your sister.

241
00:13:41,867 --> 00:13:44,733
She's hard as a rock

242
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:48,633
because it was also not easy
for her to support both of you.

243
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:51,800
But that doesn't mean that
you're worthless, Tonito.

244
00:13:53,367 --> 00:13:58,233
And so what if your sister
still sees you as loose change?

245
00:13:58,333 --> 00:14:02,167
A million won't be complete
without a loose change.

246
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:06,600
Cliché.

247
00:14:08,267 --> 00:14:12,567
And besides, have you forgotten
that back then,

248
00:14:12,633 --> 00:14:15,100
you've helped a juvenile
delinquent

249
00:14:15,167 --> 00:14:17,333
who's in and out of jail?

250
00:14:18,767 --> 00:14:24,200
The last time I checked,
he was grateful to you.

251
00:14:25,233 --> 00:14:27,667
If you didn't send him
to school,

252
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:33,633
maybe he's still in jail
or maybe he's dead.

253
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,767
And you won't be facing him
right now.

254
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,367
So don't think that you're
worthless, Tonito.

255
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:53,633
You're just full of drama.

256
00:15:16,733 --> 00:15:20,300
Maybe you can pan and then
eventually,

257
00:15:20,367 --> 00:15:23,833
do a close-up on the product
to show the product of Sorsogon.

258
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:25,133
Okay.

259
00:15:25,933 --> 00:15:27,667
Just like that.

260
00:15:27,733 --> 00:15:30,733
Celeste!

261
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,967
- Hey!
- What are you doing here?

262
00:15:33,033 --> 00:15:35,033
I brought food for you.

263
00:15:35,133 --> 00:15:37,867
This is no carbs.
I know you're on a diet.

264
00:15:39,233 --> 00:15:40,633
Thank you.

265
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:46,467
Why?

266
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:47,733
What's going on?

267
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:52,200
My new probation officer
is very strict.

268
00:15:52,267 --> 00:15:54,133
She's exaggerated.

269
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,400
Mikoy was with me
when she called.

270
00:15:57,467 --> 00:15:59,500
She said you are
a troublemaker.

271
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:01,133
Me? Troublemaker?

272
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:03,033
I'm not a troublemaker.

273
00:16:04,033 --> 00:16:06,233
She's just exaggerated.
That's what she is.

274
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:11,067
Anyway, I wish it's Mikoy again.

275
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:13,533
Huh?

276
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:15,733
What did you say, Cuz?

277
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:18,600
Do you wish it's Mikoy again?

278
00:16:18,667 --> 00:16:21,300
As in, you wish you will
get back together?

279
00:16:21,367 --> 00:16:23,133
Is that it?

280
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,200
No, silly.

281
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:26,533
Chili?

282
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,267
Are that red chilis
or chili fingers?

283
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:30,167
I have that.
I'll bring you next time.

284
00:16:30,233 --> 00:16:33,000
Anyway, what I said is,

285
00:16:33,067 --> 00:16:35,567
I wish Mikoy is my probationary
officer again

286
00:16:35,633 --> 00:16:36,633
because the other one
is annoying.

287
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:38,667
Lunch break is over.

288
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:43,100
She's so strict.

289
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:48,100
Anyway, thank you for
visiting me and the food.

290
00:16:48,167 --> 00:16:50,300
That's nothing.

291
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:54,367
By the way, you are also
not allowed to accept visitors.

292
00:17:06,167 --> 00:17:07,367
Yes, you.

293
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:08,767
Me?

294
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:10,833
Is she referring to me?

295
00:17:22,567 --> 00:17:23,767
What did you say?

296
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:25,467
So I'm not allowed to use
the phone,

297
00:17:25,533 --> 00:17:29,033
not allowed to talk to someone,
not allowed to accept visitors.

298
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,600
Am I in a labor camp?

299
00:17:30,667 --> 00:17:34,933
You know, honestly,
this is not fair anymore.

300
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,500
Who brought yourself
to this place?

301
00:17:37,567 --> 00:17:39,500
Wasn't it you?

302
00:17:39,567 --> 00:17:42,033
Who destroyed the galleon
replica?

303
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:43,600
Wasn't it you?

304
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:44,867
That was an accident.

305
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:46,033
Whether it's an accident or not,

306
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:48,600
you still have to pay
for what you did.

307
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:52,233
Now, you have a choice.

308
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:56,500
Either you follow my rules
or just go to jail.

309
00:17:58,067 --> 00:17:59,967
You choose.

310
00:18:00,033 --> 00:18:04,900
Just talk to me once you made
a decision.

311
00:18:09,633 --> 00:18:12,167
My God, she has the nerve.

312
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:14,033
So everything is my fault.

313
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:16,267
I had an accident,
this and that.

314
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,267
She talks a lot.

315
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:19,800
She blames me for everything,
annoying.

316
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:23,900
I wish I could just disappear
from this place.

317
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:08,400
What? It's okay to remove
the husk.

318
00:19:12,167 --> 00:19:13,867
Paeng, we still have a lot
of this, right?

319
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:15,000
Yes, Sir.

320
00:19:18,633 --> 00:19:19,600
Okay.

321
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:21,233
Wait, it's Mikoy.

322
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:29,400
Mikoy, you're here.

323
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:32,700
Aren't you and Celeste together?

324
00:19:32,767 --> 00:19:35,900
No, I'm on leave today.

325
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:39,133
I'm managing a livelihood
program in the city hall.

326
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,133
Is that so?

327
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:42,267
We're looking for Pili farms.

328
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:46,767
We will make the husk and
the shell into a bag.

329
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:48,233
Maybe you want to join.

330
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:50,200
That's great.

331
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:52,333
I approve of that.

332
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:53,833
That's quick.

333
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:54,833
And besides Father,

334
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:57,800
we just throw away
the Pili husk.

335
00:19:57,867 --> 00:19:59,700
Let the others use them.

336
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:03,967
Once this pushes through,

337
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:05,433
maybe it would be better
if we can ask Celeste

338
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,133
to design the bags?

339
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,933
When it comes to matters
like that,

340
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,633
you should ask her.

341
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:13,900
Aren't you and Celeste okay yet?

342
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:20,100
I can't remember when was the
last time we talked properly.

343
00:20:20,167 --> 00:20:21,967
She's been here for
a few days already.

344
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:24,833
She's been here for days

345
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:26,433
but she also carried her
resentment towards me

346
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:28,700
for several years.

347
00:20:28,767 --> 00:20:33,067
Mikoy, let's eat together.

348
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:34,000
Come.
No, it's okay.

349
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,767
I'll go back to the city hall.

350
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:39,267
- Are you sure, Mikoy?
- Yes, I'll go ahead.

351
00:20:39,333 --> 00:20:40,967
- Take care.
- You take care.

352
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:46,633
Come on.

353
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:47,700
Come on, Son.

354
00:20:52,367 --> 00:20:53,167
It looks delicious.

355
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:54,367
It smells delicious, Mother.

356
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:58,533
Come on, let's eat.

357
00:20:59,433 --> 00:21:00,700
Thank you.

358
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:05,367
This is delicious.

359
00:21:58,367 --> 00:21:59,333
Celeste!

360
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:03,767
You've crossed the line.

361
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:05,600
I will really report you.

362
00:22:08,133 --> 00:22:10,300
You are causing trouble again?

363
00:22:10,367 --> 00:22:11,367
You haven't changed.

364
00:22:11,433 --> 00:22:13,767
You are a troublemaker.

365
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:16,133
You are giving Ms. Vangie
a headache.

366
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:19,833
- Mikoy...
- Good thing I arrived.

367
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:21,367
What if I didn't arrive?

368
00:22:21,433 --> 00:22:23,167
Even Ms. Vangie who is very kind

369
00:22:23,233 --> 00:22:24,200
is running out of patience
with you.

370
00:22:24,267 --> 00:22:25,767
You should be ashamed.

371
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:28,133
Mikoy, I'm sorry.

372
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,533
I don't understand...

373
00:22:31,267 --> 00:22:34,133
Ms. Vangie, I'm sorry,
but I'll take care of her.

374
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:37,033
Don't push through with
your recommendation to Mayor.

375
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:38,700
I'll talk to Mayor

376
00:22:38,767 --> 00:22:41,333
so the punishment for this woman
is worse.

377
00:22:43,933 --> 00:22:48,733
Ms. Vangie, don't pass
me to Mikoy, please.

378
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:49,967
I'm sorry.

379
00:22:50,033 --> 00:22:55,467
Hey, now you will beg
after you fooled Ms. Vangie.

380
00:22:55,533 --> 00:22:56,467
Stop it.

381
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:58,000
I'll take care of her.

382
00:22:58,967 --> 00:23:00,633
I'm okay.

383
00:23:01,833 --> 00:23:04,567
- Come here.
- No, I'll take care of Celeste.

384
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:07,567
I'll take care of this.

385
00:23:07,633 --> 00:23:09,233
She is my responsibility.

386
00:23:09,300 --> 00:23:10,700
I'll take care of her.

387
00:23:10,767 --> 00:23:11,800
No, no.

388
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:13,200
No, don't talk anymore!

389
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:14,400
She's a woman, Mikoy.

390
00:23:14,467 --> 00:23:16,567
Don't meddle, Ms. Vangie.

391
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:17,967
I might get mad at you.

392
00:23:36,167 --> 00:23:39,533
So, it looks like you
and your stepmom

393
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:41,800
will have a bonding moment.

394
00:23:41,867 --> 00:23:43,667
Surprise, surprise!

395
00:23:43,733 --> 00:23:46,433
Aurelia brought your
favorite bakalaw dish.

396
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:49,233
Maybe you will not refuse me
this time.

397
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,367
I came here to see you.

398
00:23:50,433 --> 00:23:52,167
Focus, Mikoy.

399
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,500
This is just for documentation.

400
00:23:56,567 --> 00:23:57,667
I'll send this to Mayor.

401
00:23:57,733 --> 00:24:00,433
Guess who shared the table
with me.

402
00:24:00,500 --> 00:24:01,500
Hi, Tiff.

403
00:24:01,567 --> 00:24:02,867
Oh my gosh,
is what I'm seeing real,

404
00:24:02,933 --> 00:24:04,800
or am I just dreaming?

405
00:24:04,867 --> 00:24:06,300
You can't eat spicy food
anymore.

406
00:24:06,367 --> 00:24:07,800
- I can.
- Go ahead.

407
00:24:07,867 --> 00:24:11,800
I'll eat this but you should eat
ten chilies.

408
00:24:11,867 --> 00:24:13,467
Call, game.

409
00:24:17,967 --> 00:24:19,733
Are you and Celeste
really getting married?

410
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:20,867
Where is this coming from?

411
00:24:20,933 --> 00:24:22,633
Are you sure about her?

412
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:24,833
Mikoy is ugly here.

413
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:26,000
You talk as if...

414
00:24:26,067 --> 00:24:27,233
you're also not that beautiful
when you were young.

415
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,233
Whatever.

416
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,633
Haven't old feelings
resurfaced yet?

417
00:24:30,733 --> 00:24:32,467
Celeste already has a fiancé.

418
00:24:32,533 --> 00:24:33,667
You didn't answer my question.

419
00:24:33,733 --> 00:24:38,133
Welcome to Estrellado Pili Farm!

420
00:24:38,900 --> 00:24:39,967
What's the meaning of this?

421
00:24:40,033 --> 00:24:41,000
Your next duty is here.

422
00:24:41,067 --> 00:24:42,367
I wasn't able to contact
Tiffany.

423
00:24:42,433 --> 00:24:44,667
No matter how good of
a businessman you are,

424
00:24:44,733 --> 00:24:45,767
nothing will prepare you

425
00:24:45,833 --> 00:24:48,300
for the most difficult business
deal in your life,

426
00:24:48,367 --> 00:24:49,300
your kid.

427
00:24:49,367 --> 00:24:52,100
Can you give me some space?

428
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:56,067
More?

429
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:59,867
- Okay.
- You can't even give one day...

430
00:24:59,933 --> 00:25:01,133
for me,

431
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:04,433
for your wife who died
because of you.

432
00:25:04,533 --> 00:25:06,000
Celeste, you're getting
out of hand.

433
00:25:06,067 --> 00:25:07,300
No, you shut up.

434
00:25:07,367 --> 00:25:10,167
Have you ever seen your mother
cry herself to sleep?

435
00:25:10,233 --> 00:25:13,367
Have you ever seen her
lose her mind

436
00:25:13,433 --> 00:25:16,033
because the man of her dreams
left her?

437
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:19,300
Have you ever seen your mother
waiting under the rain

438
00:25:19,367 --> 00:25:20,467
because he never came back
to her

439
00:25:20,533 --> 00:25:22,467
because he chose his mistress?
